{
  "doc_id": "12949",
  "text": "The sequence CUAGACUAGA of the tat exon 2 ESS is similar to other known binding sequences for hnRNP A1. The UACCUUUAGAGUAGG intron element regulating 5Ј splice site selection in the human hnRNP A1 premRNA [CITATION_1] and the mouse hepatitis virus RNA transcription regulatory region UUAGAUUAGA [CITATION_2] are both bound by hnRNP A1. Utilizing the SELEX technique, [CITATION_3] have identified a 'winner' high-affinity binder RNA for hnRNP A1, UAUGAUAGGGACUUAGGGUG with an apparent K d ϭ 1ϫ10 -9 . All of these hnRNP A1-binding sequences contain tandem repeats of the sequence UAG at their core.",
